

				vim
				===
		

0.  Description.
	
	Interactive function execution trace.

1.  Operation.

	
2.  zûdefine cx

	cx = target context of VIM tool.
	z = `cx._VIM

3.  Variables

	_PRINTû		"/tmp/vim.txt"

	_BOOLEAN:	level boolean
	_N:		levels

	_COLORSû	level-based color array;
	_MATRIXû	indendented matrix
	_VIEWû		view of _MATRIX

	_ACTIONû	Level=0
			Level=Ó
			Level+1
			Level-1

	_VIMû		outer layout	
	
4.  Restrictions

	_MATRIX must be a character matrix, levels represented by single
	character indentation.

	VIM controls `set and `preset callbacks on _MATRIX, `set callback on
	_COLORS, and `set callback on _ACTION.

5.  Example

	$load s
	$load vim
	show vim.define `foo

